{"lemma":"سَعَفاتٌ","slug":"سَعَفاتٌ","root":"س.ع.ف","root_slug":"س-ع-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ع-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19840","n19841"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to aid, to rescue"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to manage (بـ (b-) or acc. something)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to happen to (acc.) someone"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be cracked, to scale off around the nail"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mix incenses with aromatic oils, to add up to the fragrance","tags":["Classical"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"palm leaves, palm branches (having leaves)","tags":["Classical","collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"utensil, commodity, article of merchandise","tags":["Classical"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"vile, mean","tags":["Classical"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19840","headword_ar":"سَعْفٌ","root":"sEf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A commodity; an article of merchandise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu saEofu sawo'K","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ سَعْفُ سَوْءٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily it is a bad commodity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man vile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mean, and despised in all his circumstances."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n19841","headword_ar":"سَعَفٌ","root":"sEf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Palm-branches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, * S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as long as they have the leaves upon them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"when these are removed from them, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jariydN","text_ar":"جَرِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"parts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of palm-branches upon which leaves have grown:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EasiybN","text_ar":"عَسِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaves of palm-branches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which are woven"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"baskets of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zubul","text_ar":"زُبُل"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zubolaAn","text_ar":"زُبْلَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) [pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zabiylN","text_ar":"زَبِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the similar receptacles called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jilaAl","text_ar":"جِلَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jul~apN","text_ar":"جُلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and fans"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which are made in the form of small flags], (Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"palm-branches themselves"},{"kind":"text","text":"are thus called: (Mgh:) accord. to Lth, (Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as have become dry"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of palm-branches"},{"kind":"text","text":"] are mostly thus called; the fresh [palm-branch] being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aTobapN","text_ar":"شَطْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, K, TA:) sing., (S,) or [rather] n. un., (Mgh, Msb,) with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh, Msb:) which also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a palm-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"itself; and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEafaAtN","text_ar":"سَعَفَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, as being likened to palm-leaves,] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forelock"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse: so in the saying of Imrael-Keys,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waA^arokabu fiY Alr~awoEi xayofaAnapF\n                      \n                     \n                        kasaA wajohahaA saEafN munota$iro"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And I ride, in war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"battle, a brisk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an agile, leaving"},{"kind":"text","text":"mare,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose face a spreading forelock has clad"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: which shows that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEafN","text_ar":"سَعَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly] signifies the leaves [of a palm-branch]. (Az, TA.) [Jac. Schultens, as mentioned by Freytag, explains it as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A whiteness upon the forehead of a horse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this explanation is perhaps conjectural, from the verse cited above.]       -A2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"paraphernalia"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jahaAz","text_ar":"جَهَاز"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a bride:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suEuwfN","text_ar":"سُعُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything good, goodly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excel-lent, and consummate, such as a slave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any precious thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a house that one possesses."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of fly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned by a poet as smiting a lion. (IB, TA.)       -A4-  See also 1."}],"source_refs":["Msb","Mgh","K","TA","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}